%p That's a whole lotta CSS, huh? Think I'm ever going back in there to pull those vendor prefixes once they're approved? Not likely. However, Compass stays on top of them so if I ever recompile the file it will irradicate unnecessary ones for me. Again, making me better than I am.

%p Now, we did some extra stuff to the new version of the button but here is the new code:

%pre
  %code.language-css
    :preserve
      button {
        @include button(#7fbf4d, #63a62f, 3px, 1px solid #63a62f);
        @include box-shadow(inset 0 1px 0 0 #96ca6d);
        border-bottom: 1px solid #5b992b;
        color: #fff;
        float: right;
        font-size: 1.5em;
        line-height: 1;
        padding: .75em 0 .8em 0;
        text-shadow: 0 -1px 0 #4c9021;
        width: 150px;
        &:hover {
          @include box-shadow(inset 0 1px 0 0 #8dbf67);
        }
        &:active {
          @include box-shadow(inset 0 0 8px 4px #548c29, 0 1px 0 0 #eeeeee);
          border: 1px solid #5b992b;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #538c27;
        } 
      }

%p Not only is that more concise, it is waaaay more powerful and extendable. We made our own button mixin that sets the things that will be on every button to be written right away. I won't go into the full breakdown here but this is the kind of code that I want to be writing. Lean and mean, man.
